The paper discusses the design and testing of a wizard system for controlling the sharing of personal information on online social networks, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also addresses concerns about privacy and the misuse of personal information, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of mobile devices to access online social networks is also mentioned, which could be classified under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the potential for upgrading current privacy systems or designing new ones, which could be classified under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
